==Most isolated major summits==
{{GeoGroup|section=Most isolated major summits}}
Of the most isolated major summits of Utah, [[Kings Peak (Utah)|Kings Peak]] exceeds {{convert|200|km|1|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}} of topographic isolation and four peaks exceed {{convert|100|km|2|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}} of topographic isolation.
{{clear}}
